The paper discusses the application of deep learning techniques to molecular design, which falls under the intersection of computer science and chemistry. The paper focuses on the use of various deep learning techniques such as recursive neural networks, autoencoders, generative adversarial networks, and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
